    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/52<hi rend="superscript">1/16</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-05T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 5, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Department’s 18, June 3, 3 p.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d164fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_19">p. 19</ref>.</note>
                    Captain Maxwell D. Taylor, U. S. Army, and Major Clayton C. Jerome, U. S. Marine
                    Corps, have been designated by the War and Navy Departments respectively to
                    undertake the confidential conversations with the Honduran authorities.</p>
                <p>They expect to arrive in San José June 10 and after terminating their
                    conversations there will proceed to Managua, Tegucigalpa, San Salvador and
                    Guatemala in the order named to undertake similar conversations.</p>
                <p>You will be advised through the Legation in Managua of the date and hour of their
                    proposed arrival in Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
